<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I find following sentence in line 515 in Zend/Mail.php.</p>

<p>$this-&gt;_storeHeader('From', $this-&gt;_encodeHeader('"'.$name.'"').' &lt;'.$email.'&gt;', true);</p>

<p>But it causes error if Sender name contains Multibyte characters and Receiver uses OutlookExpress.
For example ,  I look in the $this , =?ISO-2022-JP?Q?"=1B$BAw=3F.&lt;T=1B(B"?=.
I think it must be "=?ISO-2022-JP?Q?=1B$BAw=3F.&lt;T=1B(B?=".</p>

<p>I propose to modify the line as next.
$this-&gt;_storeHeader('From', '"'.$this-&gt;_encodeHeader($name).'"&lt;'.$email.'&gt;', true);</p>

<p>I hope it will useful.</p>

